# Root .gitignore. The deployable app lives in web/ (which has its own
# web/.gitignore for build output). This file keeps the heavy ML training assets,
# Python environments and caches OUT of the repo. Intentionally NOT ignored: the
# web app, its Drizzle migrations (web/drizzle/), the exported ONNX models in
# web/public/models/, and the training *code* (training/scripts, training/src).

# --- Python environments & caches ---
**/.venv/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
*.egg-info/

# --- Training: datasets, intermediate caches, logs and model-training artifacts.
# Large and regenerable; the web app uses the exported models in web/public/models
# instead, so none of this is needed in the repo. ---
training/.venv/
training/data/
training/quarantine/
training/downloads/
training/artifacts/
training/autolabel_report.csv
training/**/*.log

# --- OS cruft ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
